# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Database — Neon (PostgreSQL, serverless)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Development uses the Neon "development" branch connection string here.
# Production sets DATABASE_URL to the production branch.
#
# Use the POOLED connection string (host contains "-pooler") for the app at
# runtime. Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your own value.
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST-pooler.REGION.aws.neon.tech/DBNAME?sslmode=require"

# Optional: a DIRECT (non-pooled) connection for migrations / shadow database.
# Only needed if `prisma migrate dev` against the pooled URL gives you trouble.
# Add `directUrl = env("DIRECT_URL")` to the schema's datasource block to use it.
# DIRECT_URL="postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST.REGION.aws.neon.tech/DBNAME?sslmode=require"
